# V&V fixtures are byte-exact content (κ-addressed blobs, gzip'd OCI layers,
# kernels, warm κ-snapshots). They MUST NOT be line-ending-filtered: an autocrlf
# checkout on Windows rewrites LF→CRLF and corrupts a binary blob so its content no
# longer matches its sha256 name (a DigestMismatch on OCI ingest, CC-10/14/61).
# Mark every binary fixture class as binary so it round-trips byte-for-byte.
vv/artifacts/**/blobs/** binary
*.gz binary
*.kblob binary
*.img binary
*.ext4 binary
*.tar binary
vmlinux* binary
bzImage* binary
Image* binary
